{"event": "tool_call", "tool": "think", "args": {"thought": "\nKey finding: Both TC-83232 and TC-83240 show:\n```yaml\nPage snapshot:\n- img \"Loading...\" [ref=e3]\n```\n\nThis means the page was still in a loading state when the test ran. The page isn't fully loaded - it's only showing a loading spinner. This is not a selector issue - it's a page loading issue.\n\nThe UAT site seems to have issues loading sometimes. The React error #418 (hydration mismatch) I saw in the browser tool confirms this.\n\nRoot causes:\n1. **TC-83232 and TC-83240**: Page snapshot shows `img \"Loading...\"` - the page is stuck in a loading state. The navigate() method returns after `domcontentloaded` or `load` but the React/Next.js SPA hasn't hydrated yet.\n\n2. **TC-83238 (firefox/webkit)**: Store is already set (Granville & Georgia) from stored browser state. There's NO \"Set your store\" link because a store was already selected from a previous test run.\n\n**Fixes:**\n\n**For TC-83232 (newsletter) and TC-83240 (login):**\nThe page snapshot shows only `img \"Loading...\"` which means the site itself is loading slowly or is in an error state. The fix should be to:\n1. Add a `waitForLoadState('networkidle')` call after navigation in the `navigate` helper\n2. OR add a retry mechanism for the navigation\n3. OR wait for the body/h1 to be loaded before proceeding\n\nLooking at the TC-83232 test, it already does `await homePage.navigate(homePageData.urls.home)` then scrolls. But the page is stuck on loading.\n\nLooking at the TC-83240 test, it navigates to `/myaccount` which should redirect to login, but the page is stuck on loading.\n\nThe `BasePage.navigate()` method needs to be checked:\n"}}
