All three failures are fixed. Here's a summary of what changed and why:

---

**`pages/BasePage.ts`** — added `waitForAppShell()`
- After `load` state resolves, the Next.js/React SPA on the UAT origin can still be hydrating (React errors #418/#329 leave a loading spinner).
- New `waitForAppShell()` waits for `<header>` to be visible (up to 20 s) after every `navigate()` call, confirming hydration before the test proceeds.
- This fixes **TC-83232** (page snapshot was `img "Loading..."`) and **TC-83240** (same root cause).

**`pages/LoginPage.ts`** — increased email input timeout to 30 s
- The redirect from `/myaccount` to the login form takes longer on UAT than the previous 15 s budget allowed.
- Complements the `waitForAppShell()` fix in BasePage.

**`tests/home-page.spec.ts` — TC-83232 scroll loop**
- Replaced single `window.scrollTo` with a retry loop (up to 5 × 600 ms) that scrolls to the bottom and checks if the newsletter input is visible after each scroll.
- The intersection-observer-driven newsletter section needs multiple scroll triggers because the page body grows as Builder.io components render.

**`pages/ProductDetailPage.ts`** — `openStoreSelectorDialog()` dual-state handling
- In Firefox/WebKit, the geolocation permission causes the UAT site to auto-set a nearby store (Granville & Georgia), replacing the "Set your store" link with "Check Availability at other stores".
- The method now checks with a 3 s probe: if "Set your store" is not visible, it falls back to clicking "Check Availability at other stores", which opens the same `dialog#store-selector`. Also scrolls the `inStorePickupRadio` into view first to ensure the section is rendered.
- Fixes **TC-83238** on Firefox and WebKit.
